cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY

The paper discusses a countermeasure against cache timing attacks, which is a common security concern in computer systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a software-based countermeasure, which suggests that it may fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the countermeasure, which may fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the countermeasure in financial, military, and government systems, which suggests that it may fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
